### 2. The Widget Layout (`widget_layout.xml`)

To make the emoticon take up 90% of the available space, we'll use a `RelativeLayout` (or `FrameLayout`) and set the `textSize` of the `TextView` containing the emoticon to a very large value. Since `RemoteViews` for widgets don't easily support percentage-based sizing, we use a large, size-relative unit like `sp` or rely on the `TextView`'s alignment within the full-sized layout.

```xml
<RelativeLayout 
    xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    android:id="@+id/widget_root_layout"
    android:layout_width="match_parent"
    android:layout_height="match_parent"
    android:background="@drawable/widget_background_shape" 
    android:padding="8dp" > <TextView
        android:id="@+id/emoticon_text_view"
        android:layout_width="wrap_content"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:layout_centerInParent="true"
        
        android:textSize="72sp" 
        android:textAlignment="center"
        android:textStyle="normal"
        android:textColor="@android:color/black"
        
        android:text="?" /> 

</RelativeLayout>
                              
